<subSubSection id="C3716530FFEFFFA575EEF85AFAA04EAE" box="[199,1406,1996,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD436BBFFEFFFA575EEF85AFAA04EAE" blockId="1.[151,1436,1580,2020]" box="[199,1406,1996,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B91FEAA9FFEFFFA575EEF85AFE994EA9" bold="true" box="[199,327,1996,2020]" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D38FFEFFFA57642F85AFC6A4EAE" box="[875,948,1996,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Connectivus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis id="B91FEAA9FFEFFFA57642F85AFC6A4EAE" box="[875,948,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="86">bifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the apex forked of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
